last resort for the fellas

33:23.108 --> 33:24.642
when they're, you know, donating.

33:24.643 --> 33:26.880
Go on, rip off the wrapper
and see what the problem is.

33:32.519 --> 33:36.053
Why is a girl in a bathing
suit wrapped in brown paper?

33:36.054 --> 33:37.989
'Cause it's good for circulation.

33:37.990 --> 33:39.590
But the magazine itself, it's a dog.

33:39.591 --> 33:40.994
The guys need more skin.

33:40.995 --> 33:42.395
So I'm canceling it.

33:47.934 --> 33:50.102
Hello?

33:52.339 --> 33:56.341
Um, I brought some dinner
for you and Joy...

33:56.342 --> 33:58.644
Unless the caretaker--

33:58.645 --> 34:00.280
No, I fired the caretaker.

34:02.882 --> 34:05.884
It looks like you
had good reason to.

34:05.885 --> 34:07.420
No, not really.

34:10.023 --> 34:14.023
I was just, um, watching her
get Joy dressed this morning,

34:15.061 --> 34:19.061
and it occurred to me that, um,
Joy's birthday is next week.

34:20.500 --> 34:22.001
So I thought, "What should I do?

34:22.002 --> 34:25.904
Should I plan a party
or buy her a present?"

34:25.905 --> 34:28.507
And then suddenly I...

34:28.507 --> 34:32.507
All I wanted was that nurse gone.

34:35.081 --> 34:39.452
I just wanted to be alone
with her, just the two of us.

34:42.522 --> 34:45.090
I understand.

34:45.091 --> 34:47.059
Um, that must be--

34:47.060 --> 34:48.995
It's a nightmare.
That's what it is.

34:50.496 --> 34:52.998
And you want to know the real truth? Um...

34:54.900 --> 34:58.071
I don't see why I should
buy Joy anything...

35:01.474 --> 35:03.443
'cause she's already gone.

35:05.945 --> 35:08.113
It's like she's dead.

35:08.114 --> 35:12.114
It's like sitting here day and night...

35:13.453 --> 35:16.154
with a corpse.

35:16.155 --> 35:18.123
A corpse?

35:18.124 --> 35:21.093
What a terrible thing to say.

35:21.094 --> 35:22.495
Joy is sitting right here.

35:22.496 --> 35:25.063
You have no idea what she knows

35:25.064 --> 35:28.100
or what she feels or cares or-- or hears.

35:28.101 --> 35:32.237
For you to just write her
off like that is criminal.

35:32.238 --> 35:34.605
Joy is the woman that you
married all these years ago,

35:34.606 --> 35:38.342
and you have to remember and
honor who she is-- still.

35:38.343 --> 35:44.509
Treat her with the same dignity
and respect that you always did.

35:47.587 --> 35:49.455
We're gonna give her a bath...

35:49.456 --> 35:51.323
Together...

35:51.324 --> 35:52.491
Now.

35:55.962 --> 35:58.565
Whew.

36:01.100 --> 36:04.236
Your elevator's out.

36:04.237 --> 36:07.139
I was worried you weren't eating enough.

36:07.140 --> 36:09.240
Now I understand those
four flights of stairs

36:09.241 --> 36:10.508
are what's keeping you so thin.

36:12.379 --> 36:13.645
Beef bourguignon.

36:13.646 --> 36:15.314
May I come in?

36:15.315 --> 36:17.549
Of course.

36:17.550 --> 36:19.319
Sorry. I'm not much of a housekeeper.

36:19.320 --> 36:22.588
As if that's news to me.

36:22.589 --> 36:26.024
It's very... pleasant.

36:26.025 --> 36:27.627
"Pleasant."

36:27.628 --> 36:29.361
That word.

36:29.362 --> 36:31.963
Whenever we'd go to a restaurant
and you didn't like your meal,

36:31.964 --> 36:33.564
you'd always smile and
say, "It's very pleasant."

36:34.967 --> 36:37.468
Well, this time I mean it's pleasant.

36:37.469 --> 36:39.403
Knowing you, I was worried you'd
take the first place you saw.

36:39.404 --> 36:41.040
This was the first place.

36:43.276 --> 36:45.009
Why don't I put that in the fridge?

36:45.010 --> 36:46.379
Why don't I
put it in the fridge,

36:46.380 --> 36:48.581
and you make us a drink?

36:54.087 --> 36:56.956
Your gentleman
friend seems very nice.

36:56.957 --> 37:00.359
Quite a firm handshake.

37:00.360 --> 37:03.295
Sorry about how that happened.

37:03.296 --> 37:05.898
I'll be honest--
I'm not sure what to think,

37:05.899 --> 37:07.532
given you and this man

37:07.533 --> 37:10.201
have cause to see Bill
and Virginia already.

37:10.202 --> 37:13.237
Has it occurred to you that you
might not be ideally suited?

37:13.238 --> 37:16.007
And how long
should Graham and I

37:16.008 --> 37:18.011
wait to address our
sexual issues, Barton?

37:18.012 --> 37:19.011
30 years?

37:19.012 --> 37:21.179
No, of course not.

37:21.180 --> 37:23.583
I just want you to be happy, Margaret.

37:25.051 --> 37:28.053
Well, I actually think I've found a way.

37:28.054 --> 37:32.054
And it starts with telling
the truth about everything.

37:33.026 --> 37:35.260
Who's J?

37:35.261 --> 37:36.361
J?

37:36.362 --> 37:38.162
All those dishes
in the refrigerator

37:38.163 --> 37:39.365
with instructions taped to them--

37:39.366 --> 37:43.335
"Reheat in a 350-degree oven
for 15 minutes. Love, J"?

37:43.336 --> 37:45.871
Who's J?

37:45.872 --> 37:48.607
Mm. Is it a man?

37:48.608 --> 37:50.609
"J" is Judith.

37:50.610 --> 37:53.444
She lives in the building. She
leaves me dinner sometimes.

37:53.445 --> 37:54.912
And notes with hearts.

37:54.913 --> 37:56.447
It doesn't mean
anything, Margaret.

37:56.448 --> 37:59.183
Not to you, perhaps,
but what do you mean to her?

37:59.184 --> 38:01.118
We're friends. We
enjoy each other's company.

38:01.119 --> 38:02.488
I took her to dinner on New Year's.

38:02.489 --> 38:03.889
We play Cribbage.

38:03.890 --> 38:06.458
Does she know?

38:06.459 --> 38:07.492
About you?

38:07.493 --> 38:10.429
You mean what kind of man I am?

38:10.430 --> 38:13.099
That I'm the kind who can't
cook, who can't keep house,

38:13.100 --> 38:15.934
who, after a failed marriage of 30 years

38:15.935 --> 38:19.505
is grateful for the friendship
of a-- a nice middle-aged woman

38:19.506 --> 38:23.075
who occasionally stops by with meatloaf

38:23.076 --> 38:25.209
and stays to watch "Perry Mason"?

38:25.210 --> 38:27.311
And after "Perry Mason"?

38:27.312 --> 38:29.480
Not that it's any
of your business, Margaret,

38:29.481 --> 38:31.916
but we're not having a
sexual relationship.

38:31.917 --> 38:33.918
Well, neither were you and I.

38:33.919 --> 38:36.620
Now, I understand why you can't
be honest with your daughter,

38:36.621 --> 38:38.324
and I pay the price every
time I call Vivian

38:38.325 --> 38:39.891
and she hangs up on me,

38:39.892 --> 38:42.993
but this woman, this new woman,
she deserves to know the truth.

38:42.994 --> 38:45.062
She deserves to know what kind
of future she can expect.

38:45.063 --> 38:46.499
You're out of line, Margaret.

38:46.500 --> 38:47.599
Why?

38:47.600 --> 38:50.201
Why are you the only one
who gets a choice in this?

38:50.202 --> 38:52.336
What are you talking about?
You moved on.

38:52.337 --> 38:53.537
With-- with what's-his-name.

38:53.538 --> 38:55.072
Well, then let
me tell him the truth.

38:55.073 --> 38:56.874
Let me tell him why our marriage ended.

38:56.875 --> 39:00.876
How I choose to conduct
my private life is my business,

39:00.913 --> 39:02.914
and mine only.

39:02.915 --> 39:06.918
Barton, what have you and I

39:06.919 --> 39:09.354
learned through all of our pain

39:09.355 --> 39:12.524
if you're lying to a woman
who cares about you

39:12.525 --> 39:14.126
and I can't tell Graham

39:14.127 --> 39:17.596
why sex is the only way I
know that he loves me?

39:17.597 --> 39:20.499
Tell Judith.

39:20.500 --> 39:23.235
Let me tell Graham.

39:23.236 --> 39:27.272
You're asking too much, Margaret.

39:27.273 --> 39:29.375
I'm sorry.

39:35.014 --> 39:38.150
Oh, for the love of God...

39:38.151 --> 39:40.019
Nice to see you again, Leslie.

39:40.020 --> 39:41.153
Really?

39:41.154 --> 39:43.354
'Cause I'm not sure it's so nice at all.

39:43.355 --> 39:45.324
I do think we can agree

39:45.325 --> 39:49.227
that a little controversy
can be a good thing.

39:49.228 --> 39:50.529
Can't it?

39:50.530 --> 39:51.997
Drive sales.

39:51.998 --> 39:54.999
Certainly didn't hurt "Women
In Love" or "Lolita," did it?

39:55.000 --> 39:57.870
If you're comparing
those books to your book,

39:57.871 --> 39:59.404
your book isn't dirty.

39:59.405 --> 40:02.406
Believe me, I read your book
before I agreed to stock it.

40:02.407 --> 40:04.143
You're absolutely correct.

40:04.144 --> 40:07.112
But what if people thought it were?

40:07.113 --> 40:11.113
What I'm proposing is that
you take every last copy

40:12.585 --> 40:13.985
you have left,

40:13.986 --> 40:17.022
wrap it up in plain brown paper,

40:17.023 --> 40:19.358
and create a display for the front window.

40:19.359 --> 40:21.059
And?

40:21.060 --> 40:22.294
And watch.

40:22.295 --> 40:24.195
With no sign, no explanation,

40:24.196 --> 40:26.297
curiosity will get the better of people.

40:26.298 --> 40:28.234
You tell someone he can't have something,

40:28.235 --> 40:30.168
suddenly it's all he wants.

40:30.169 --> 40:33.239
Next thing, people are in the
store asking a question,

40:33.240 --> 40:34.472
making a purchase.

40:34.473 --> 40:36.242
With all due respect,

40:36.243 --> 40:40.045
you're a scientist, not a salesman.

40:40.046 --> 40:42.514
Just test me and-- and see.

40:42.515 --> 40:44.049
Try it.

40:44.050 --> 40:48.050
And if it doesn't lead
to increased sales, I'll, um...

40:49.322 --> 40:51.257
I'll buy every last copy.

40:56.028 --> 40:59.029
"Wouldn't you like a magic
phrase to stop arguments,

40:59.030 --> 41:01.165
end ill feelings, create goodwill,

41:01.166 --> 41:03.369
and make the other person feel better?

41:03.370 --> 41:05.604
Yes? All right, here it is.

41:05.605 --> 41:09.605
Say, 'I don't blame you one
iota for feeling as you do.

41:10.476 --> 41:13.645
I understand how you feel.'"

41:23.956 --> 41:25.424
I've been meaning to come over, Paul.

41:27.426 --> 41:30.896
I wanted you to know that,
uh, I looked into it,

41:30.897 --> 41:33.465
and in neurology, Dolan is the best.

41:33.466 --> 41:35.167
There's no one better.

41:41.274 --> 41:43.975
I-I understand how you feel.

41:47.380 --> 41:50.249
You can't
begin to know how I feel.

41:52.351 --> 41:55.120
My life is over.

41:55.121 --> 41:57.289
It's just fucking over.

41:57.290 --> 42:00.025
There's nothing left.

42:00.026 --> 42:02.160
I have nothing left.

42:32.358 --> 42:33.993
You're home early.

42:33.994 --> 42:36.428
Uh, yes.

42:36.429 --> 42:37.496
I, uh...

42:40.399 --> 42:43.202
I'll, uh-- I'll
have dinner shortly.

42:45.104 --> 42:48.606
I was thinking today, um,

42:48.607 --> 42:50.943
about when you were first
named head of the department

42:50.944 --> 42:52.143
at Maternity.

42:52.144 --> 42:55.381
You-- you thought the
position had gone to Carlisle,

42:55.382 --> 42:58.016
and then they handed you the job.

42:58.017 --> 43:01.320
Yes. That was, um...

43:03.089 --> 43:04.522
a long time ago.

43:04.523 --> 43:08.523
And you wanted to celebrate.

43:09.061 --> 43:12.964
We wanted, the two of us,
to celebrate together...

43:12.965 --> 43:17.068
because you said that I had been--

43:17.069 --> 43:20.572
I remember you used the
word "instrumental"

43:20.573 --> 43:23.174
in helping you win the job.

43:23.175 --> 43:24.610
You were instrumental.

43:28.114 --> 43:31.449
Do you remember what you did?

43:31.450 --> 43:35.450
I... took us out to dinner.

43:36.088 --> 43:38.223
I think I-I bought

43:38.224 --> 43:44.321
the most expensive bottle
of champagne on the list.

44:06.986 --> 44:08.586
It's the army.

44:08.587 --> 44:10.554
They like to keep you waiting,
remind you who's in charge.

44:10.555 --> 44:11.924
Well, I had no idea

44:11.925 --> 44:15.460
that we would be waiting for two hours.

44:15.461 --> 44:17.361
I'm sorry. I know I dragged you here.

44:17.362 --> 44:19.196
You didn't. I volunteered.

44:19.197 --> 44:21.098
And my assistants can hold down the fort.

44:22.169 --> 44:24.437
You mean Snap, Crackle, and Pop?

44:27.339 --> 44:29.208
God, you are so like her...

44:29.209 --> 44:31.076
A girl I used to know.

44:32.945 --> 44:34.579
Here it comes again.

44:34.580 --> 44:37.983
The old Dan Logan charm.

44:40.086 --> 44:43.321
Again, my apologies.

44:43.322 --> 44:44.457
That wasn't a line, by the way.

44:44.458 --> 44:46.291
It's true.

44:46.292 --> 44:49.327
She had dark hair like you.

44:49.328 --> 44:53.298
And a brother who hadn't
made it home from France.

44:53.299 --> 44:55.367
I met her at a USO dance.

44:57.536 --> 44:59.336
You were probably still in grade school.

44:59.337 --> 45:00.938
I used to go to USO dances.

45:00.939 --> 45:02.975
Oh, so you are old
enough to remember?

45:02.976 --> 45:04.242
Barely.

45:04.243 --> 45:06.278
I was 18, when it ended.

45:08.514 --> 45:12.514
She was the only girl in the
room I wanted to dance with.

45:13.285 --> 45:15.521
But I hadn't been to
Arthur Murray at that point,

45:15.522 --> 45:18.256
and the dance floor was crowded.

45:18.257 --> 45:21.159
Nearly broke the poor thing's ankle.

45:24.196 --> 45:26.564
But she just laughed.

45:26.565 --> 45:28.900
She put her arms around my neck

45:28.901 --> 45:30.467
and made me carry her off the dance floor.

45:30.468 --> 45:33.370
She told me later she liked
being the center of attention.

45:33.371 --> 45:35.441
Didn't care what anyone else thought.

45:38.144 --> 45:41.446
There's something very...

45:41.447 --> 45:44.316
intoxicating about a woman like that.

45:46.886 --> 45:49.254
What happened to her?

45:49.255 --> 45:52.924
I still had six months
before I shipped out.

45:52.925 --> 45:55.927
We didn't let the time go to waste.

45:55.928 --> 45:57.327
And after the war?

45:57.328 --> 45:59.596
After the war, it
was back to real life.

45:59.597 --> 46:02.234
And back to
the girlfriend at home.

46:02.235 --> 46:04.036
Back to my wife.

46:10.276 --> 46:13.211
But that girl...

46:13.212 --> 46:15.914
- Did you love her?
- Very much.

46:15.915 --> 46:17.247
Then how does a man

46:17.248 --> 46:19.185
just walk away back to his fiancÃ£Â©e?

46:19.186 --> 46:20.519
Wife.

46:24.056 --> 46:27.659
Maybe you were afraid.

46:27.660 --> 46:31.660
Afraid that if you ran off with that...
dazzling girl...

46:34.099 --> 46:36.233
that you would never really measure up.

46:36.234 --> 46:39.004
If that's how you
want your story to end.

46:39.005 --> 46:41.973
But I never gave her the chance

46:41.974 --> 46:46.344
to see that the Dan Logan
charm wears thin...

46:46.345 --> 46:48.012
or so I'm told.

46:48.013 --> 46:49.515
And your wife?

46:49.516 --> 46:51.482
Is still my wife.

46:51.483 --> 46:53.586
And still none the wiser.

46:53.587 --> 46:55.553
No.

46:55.554 --> 46:57.556
Much wiser.

46:59.491 --> 47:00.993
He's ready for you.

47:07.132 --> 47:09.134
I had the worst day imaginable.

47:09.135 --> 47:11.970
I didn't know who else to call.

47:11.971 --> 47:14.039
I'm glad you called.

47:16.342 --> 47:18.010
Matt...

47:21.914 --> 47:25.550
Okay.

47:25.551 --> 47:27.619
So, what happened today?

47:27.620 --> 47:29.254
It was awful.

47:29.255 --> 47:31.223
Did you get suspended again?

47:31.224 --> 47:34.259
I found out something...

47:34.260 --> 47:37.161
really bad about my mother.

47:37.162 --> 47:40.898
Did you find one of
those dildos in her bedroom?

47:40.899 --> 47:44.068
Did you walk in on her with some guy?

47:44.069 --> 47:47.373
Please tell me that you read
some weird fantasy in her diary.

47:47.374 --> 47:50.008
You know what, Matt?

47:50.009 --> 47:53.212
I'm really not in the mood
to talk about it after all.

47:56.148 --> 47:58.249
Geez.

47:58.250 --> 48:00.885
Tessa.

48:00.886 --> 48:04.289
You want to talk,
you don't want to talk.

48:04.290 --> 48:07.925
I mean, I'm trying here.

48:07.926 --> 48:09.460
But make up your mind.

48:09.461 --> 48:12.631
My mind's already made up.

48:14.033 --> 48:15.934
So, why don't you undo your belt,

48:15.935 --> 48:18.137
and I'll put my mouth on you?

48:21.240 --> 48:23.107
Yeah?

48:23.108 --> 48:24.876
Why not?

48:32.618 --> 48:36.454
You obviously misunderstood me.

48:36.455 --> 48:38.588
We had an agreement. And that was--

48:38.589 --> 48:40.259
I understood the agreement.

48:40.260 --> 48:42.026
And I did it.

48:42.027 --> 48:45.263
And then it worked, just as you said.

48:45.264 --> 48:46.665
You've sold out?

48:46.666 --> 48:50.302
Every last copy.

48:54.139 --> 48:55.873
Oh, I'm sorry.

48:55.874 --> 48:57.874
I just can't-- I can't go home yet.

48:57.875 --> 48:59.576
I don't want my daughter
to see me like this.

48:59.577 --> 49:02.112
Well, at least he
doesn't have malaria.

49:02.113 --> 49:04.216
Oh, and alcohol
poisoning is better?

49:04.217 --> 49:07.919
Sweating, nausea.

49:07.920 --> 49:10.153
Why don't they just call
it "drank himself stupid"?

49:10.154 --> 49:11.588
Well, kids are stupid at that age,

49:11.589 --> 49:13.258
and he's on his own for the first time--

49:13.259 --> 49:14.592
Exactly.

49:14.593 --> 49:16.960
A boy who can't even hold his liquor

49:16.961 --> 49:19.331
has now volunteered for a combat unit?

49:19.332 --> 49:21.933
And they let him?

49:21.934 --> 49:24.435
Why didn't they call me? Tell me?

49:24.436 --> 49:25.636
He's 18.

49:25.637 --> 49:26.937
Henry promised me

49:26.938 --> 49:28.939
that he would not take a combat position.

49:28.940 --> 49:32.275
We had a deal that he would
scrub latrines, do laundry.

49:32.276 --> 49:34.044
Just 'cause he's in a combat unit

49:34.045 --> 49:35.278
doesn't mean he's not gonna be okay.

49:35.279 --> 49:36.382
You don't know him.

49:36.383 --> 49:39.952
Henry cried when Bambi's mother died.

49:41.987 --> 49:45.157
He used to hide under the
covers during thunderstorms.

49:45.158 --> 49:47.658
But he's a soldier now.

49:47.659 --> 49:49.661
And you know what a soldier does?

49:51.330 --> 49:53.965
He gets through the day.

49:53.966 --> 49:55.366
That's it.

49:55.367 --> 49:59.202
He wakes up, makes his bed, eats
his breakfast, does his work.

49:59.203 --> 50:01.171
He doesn't wonder what's
gonna happen tomorrow.

50:01.172 --> 50:03.876
He doesn't look around the bend
to see what's coming next week.

50:06.445 --> 50:09.080
He lives one moment to the next,

50:09.081 --> 50:10.447
and at the end of the day, goes to bed.

50:10.448 --> 50:12.184
And when he wakes up in the morning,

50:12.185 --> 50:15.253
he does it all over again...

50:15.254 --> 50:19.254
because anything else
is either speculation

50:20.125 --> 50:23.162
or suffering a future pain
that will likely never happen.

50:31.537 --> 50:33.471
One second after another--

50:33.472 --> 50:35.305
that's how I got through the war.

50:35.306 --> 50:38.143
That's how your son's
getting through the war.

50:40.279 --> 50:44.882
And that's how you'll
get through this war...

50:44.883 --> 50:47.152
'cause it's the only way.

51:17.216 --> 51:19.649
...alone in this house
if you aren't married.

51:19.650 --> 51:22.953
Well, it's a family home,
and I'm the last of the family.

51:22.954 --> 51:25.021
The dishes are in the rack.

51:25.022 --> 51:27.459
That lovely beef stew saved for leftovers.

51:28.927 --> 51:31.194
Who did you say made that for you?

51:31.195 --> 51:33.198
One of the girls at the office.

51:36.468 --> 51:38.170
They, uh...

51:40.939 --> 51:43.141
Why don't I walk you up to your apartment?

51:43.142 --> 51:45.543
Or...

51:45.544 --> 51:48.412
I left some extra food out for the cat.

51:48.413 --> 51:52.413
I don't think she'd miss me too
much if I stayed the night.

51:57.189 --> 51:59.322
Oh, I'm sorry. I've shocked you.

51:59.323 --> 52:00.323
No, no.

52:00.324 --> 52:01.627
Not at all.

52:04.162 --> 52:06.397
I don't know how to say this,

52:06.398 --> 52:08.534
but I think I owe it to you to be honest.

52:08.535 --> 52:11.869
You're still in
love with your ex-wife.

52:11.870 --> 52:15.870
No, that's not, uh...

52:16.208 --> 52:19.143
No.

52:19.144 --> 52:22.046
There were...

52:22.047 --> 52:24.149
some difficulties in our marriage,

52:24.150 --> 52:26.985
problems that still exist with me.

52:31.957 --> 52:33.358
I'm, uh...

52:38.597 --> 52:40.498
Uh...

52:40.499 --> 52:42.567
I'm on medication...

52:42.568 --> 52:45.202
for high blood pressure.

52:45.203 --> 52:47.505
Comes with certain side effects.

52:47.506 --> 52:51.506
Oh, I see.

52:52.077 --> 52:53.211
I haven't wanted to tell you

52:53.212 --> 52:57.315
because I've been enjoying
your company so much.

52:57.316 --> 52:58.983
And, uh, nowadays,

52:58.984 --> 53:01.386
women seem to think that
sex is so important.

53:01.387 --> 53:02.988
Yep.

53:04.957 --> 53:07.525
Not all women.

53:10.262 --> 53:12.331
Oh!

53:14.399 --> 53:16.367
Do I have the wrong night?

53:16.368 --> 53:17.969
It's...

53:17.970 --> 53:20.237
Thursday.

53:20.238 --> 53:21.972
I'm sorry, Jo.

53:21.973 --> 53:23.575
I thought it was Friday.

53:23.576 --> 53:25.876
Is that nightie new?

53:25.877 --> 53:27.279
It looks pretty on you.

53:27.280 --> 53:29.013
Doesn't it, Graham?

53:29.014 --> 53:30.082
Come here.

53:38.323 --> 53:39.558
Sleep well, Magpie.

53:39.559 --> 53:41.425
You too.

53:41.426 --> 53:43.328
Both of you.

53:45.297 --> 53:47.298
Lights on or off?

53:47.299 --> 53:49.067
Off, please.

54:26.872 --> 54:28.340
Hello?

54:31.476 --> 54:33.944
Hello?

54:33.945 --> 54:35.279
Bill.

54:35.280 --> 54:38.215
Uh...

54:38.216 --> 54:41.153
I'm sorry, but tonight's
not really a good night.

54:41.154 --> 54:42.253
Tessa's here.

54:42.254 --> 54:43.355
Oh, I-I know.

54:43.356 --> 54:47.259
I-I just wanted to--
wanted to talk to you.

54:49.027 --> 54:51.561
- About?
- Some good news.

54:51.562 --> 54:54.232
Uh, Little, Brown have agreed
to a second run of our book.

54:54.233 --> 54:56.200
That's fantastic.

54:56.201 --> 55:00.201
Does that mean that we are
moving ahead with the tour?

55:00.939 --> 55:03.608
Uh, actually, the more
I thought about the tour,

55:03.609 --> 55:07.611
the more I realized it may
not be, uh, the best time

55:07.612 --> 55:10.482
for you to be on the road.

55:11.950 --> 55:15.119
Uh, well, it's not ideal.

55:15.120 --> 55:19.356
So instead, we're gonna
try a new marketing strategy--

55:19.357 --> 55:23.327
wrapping the books in brown paper.

55:23.328 --> 55:25.895
It's a way of eliciting
curiosity from the public...

55:25.896 --> 55:28.633
Selling the book as
something mysterious...

55:28.634 --> 55:29.600
Illicit, even.

55:29.601 --> 55:31.001
Really?

55:31.002 --> 55:35.002
Why I'm really
here, though, is, um...

55:36.308 --> 55:37.642
Uh, to talk to you about Henry.

55:37.643 --> 55:39.910
Have you heard anything more?

55:39.911 --> 55:41.644
Maybe we could call someone.

55:41.645 --> 55:43.315
You know-- to get a definitive answer.

55:43.316 --> 55:47.084
Actually, I've
already taken care of it.

55:47.085 --> 55:49.386
It's not what I thought it was.

55:49.387 --> 55:51.956
So he's-- he's not sick.

55:51.957 --> 55:54.192
Well, that-- that's-- that's good news.

55:56.394 --> 55:59.363
Uh, also, I've, um...

55:59.364 --> 56:02.533
I realized that, um...

56:02.534 --> 56:06.871
that this gift-- the coat, I mean--

56:06.872 --> 56:10.241
was a surprise to you...

56:10.242 --> 56:14.242
and an odd gesture-- for me, anyway...

56:15.046 --> 56:18.649
Fur being the kind of thing a-a man...

56:18.650 --> 56:22.650
uh, buys for his wife.

56:23.889 --> 56:25.156
Um...

56:25.157 --> 56:27.191
You know, to be honest, I...

56:27.192 --> 56:31.192
I-I was reading this, uh, silly book.

56:31.997 --> 56:35.032
A huge best-seller, of course.

56:35.033 --> 56:37.433
An advice book that goes
about as deep as a thimble.

56:37.434 --> 56:41.006
Um, you can't believe the things
on the bookshelves these--

56:41.007 --> 56:44.909
Um, all that aside...

56:44.910 --> 56:47.011
I meant what I said.

56:47.012 --> 56:51.012
None of our success would
have happened without you.

56:52.150 --> 56:56.150
So why-- why shouldn't you wear something

56:57.055 --> 56:58.989
that makes you feel good?

56:58.990 --> 57:03.328
It's gorgeous, Bill...

57:05.297 --> 57:07.064
and so generous.

57:07.065 --> 57:08.399
But I...

57:08.400 --> 57:13.695
Look, tonight we have
several things to celebrate--

57:13.730 --> 57:17.641
the second run of our book,
Henry now malaria-free.

57:17.642 --> 57:21.079
So I-I was wondering, have you eaten?

57:24.416 --> 57:25.916
No.

57:25.917 --> 57:29.087
Can I take you to dinner?

57:32.457 --> 57:33.891
All right.

57:33.892 --> 57:36.428
Good.

57:37.596 --> 57:41.596
There's, uh, kind of a chill in the air.

57:42.300 --> 57:44.001
If only you had a coat.

